    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-04T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="76"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00 (<gloss target="#t_P1">P</gloss>)/4–1548:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Mission for Aid to Greece</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential   us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-04T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 4, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gama1">Gama</gloss> 885. For Griswold and Rankin.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d76fn1">This telegram was sent jointly to the Embassy in Greece as
                        No. 720.</note> Re <gloss target="#t_Gama1">Gama</gloss> 872, <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> [<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Deptel</hi>
                    </gloss>] 706.<note n="2" xml:id="d76fn2">This joint telegram to <gloss
                            target="#t_AMAG1">AMAG</gloss> and the Embassy, dated June 3, not
                        printed.</note> House Appropriations Committee report recommends cut
                    Grk-Turk military funds to $200 million, justifying recommendation <pb
                        facs="0123" n="103" xml:id="pg_103"/> on (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)
                    assumption guerrilla warfare will be successfully concluded in late 1948, which
                    would permit curtailment of military assistance, and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                    existence of substantial “unobligated” balance of fiscal 1948 funds as of April
                    30, 1948. Dept providing full info concerning dangers of assumption under (<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>), and pointing out that legal obligation figure does
                    not reflect true status of funds since all are committed. Dept emphasizing full
                    $275 million needed to assure success of program, and pointing out obvious
                    dangers of any lesser amount.<note n="3" xml:id="d76fn3">Thus, on June 10 and
                        14, respectively, the Department sent appropriate letters to Senators Styles
                        Bridges and Henry Cabot Lodge, Jr. (800.FAA/6–1048, 868.00/6–1448).</note>
                    Will keep you informed of developments.</p>
                <p>Wld be helpful in future discussions with Congressional leaders or in
                    communications to Congress if Griswold as Chief of <gloss target="#t_AMAG1"
                        >AMAG</gloss> wld telegraph his reaction proposed reduction, based on
                    discussions with Van Fleet.<note n="4" xml:id="d76fn4">The Department sent a
                        parallel telegram (No. 277) to Ambassador Wilson the same day
                        (868.00/6–448).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
